.TH "vmw_host_get_guestinfo" 9 "vmw_host_get_guestinfo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_host_get_guestinfo \- Gets a GuestInfo parameter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_host_get_guestinfo
.BI "(const char *guest_info_param "  ","
.BI "char *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t *length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "guest_info_param" 12
Parameter to get, e.g. GuestInfo.svga.gl3
.IP "buffer" 12
if NULL, *reply_len will contain reply size.
.IP "length" 12
size of the reply_buf.  Set to size of reply upon return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Gets the value of a  GuestInfo.* parameter.  The value returned will be in
a string, and it is up to the caller to post-process.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success
